<TITLE> Classes resume at DMC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 11 (bdnews24.com)Academic activities at Dhaka Medical College resumed Saturday after an 11-day closure following the death of a Bangladesh Chhatra League leader. Students attended classes and sat scheduled exams, said authorities. Some students injured in the March 30 clashes were also seen on the campus. The college hostels reopened on Friday for returning students after an Academic Council meeting earlier in the week decided to reopen the college. The authorities declared the institution closed for an indefinite period on the night of March 30 following fierce clashes between two BCL factions that left DMC's BCL unit general secretary Abul Asad Rajib dead and many others injured. The BCL central committee has since banned all activities of its college unit. b
